# Ticket answering procedures
**One problem per one ticket**
Always ask client to open a new ticket for every new issue. Do not discuss more then one issues in a single ticket, this will cause confusion between different issue and you will not able to working.

Secondly more and more issues in one ticket will cause more and more replies and if some one else need to reply that ticket, then he/she will need to read all the replies which will take some time more then 45-60 min which is just a wastage of time.

Refer to pre made reply to check what you need to  reply in this case

**Merge duplicate tickets**

If customer open multiple tickets for one issue, then merge those tickets.

Kayako has an option to "merge" tickets.

If customer open multiple tickets for "one issue" then use this feature to merge tickets, to avoid confusion of replying same in all tickets or closing those additional duplicate tickets. since some times customer just dont understand that he do not need to open multiple tickets, even if we explain this to him, and closing additional tickets will send "survey" email to customer, which may result in getting bad survey from customer since the issue would actually "not resolved". Plus some times we ask for something from customer, and customer reply by opening a new ticket, that way it become difficult for another tech to track the reply from multiple tickets. Merging make it easy to handle.

**Close order tickets after client confirm that he received the welcome letter**

Close the order tickets after client confirms that he/she received the welcome letter. Do not let the client report any technical issue in the order ticket. Always ask to open new ticket.

**Always Close the welcome Emails**
Welcome emails, when sent, are to be closed inmediately. Do not let the client start replying back in that ticket for problems, etc.

**Do not do exception with clients**
Do not do the exception for any client, because if you will do the one, client will ask for more and more

**Do not waste time on complicated issues**
Do not waste the time to work on complicated issues without remote hand service payment. Complicate issue including, moving the databases from old hosting accounts to new hosting accounts, moving websites specially for Shared hosting client

Read the support pages for more detail - http://www.serverpoint.com/en/dedicated-server/managed-dedicated-hosting.phtml

**Ask more and more information related to the problem**
Always ask more and more information related to the problem so that it will be helpful to diagnose the problem.

Support if Someone reports a problem related to a URL (slow, CGI/PHP errors, etc), the first thing you have to ask the client is for the URL. Don't start doing tests without that. Once you get the URL, then test. If you had done that with this ticket, you would have done a download from one of our test servers and would have seen that the download is fast.

**Do not let the Customer feels that he is not being taken care of**
Do not let the customer feels that he/she is not being taken care of. Do not provide temporary solution like if client report that his server is keep crashing every day then do not just reboot the server. Try to find the root of the problem and if its not related to distro and related to some third party software which client is using then ask client to pay remote hand service if he want us to fix it.

**Do not let the customer to open ticket with wrong department**
Departmental division in the Ticket panel is to make the work easy therefore do not let the customer open ticket with wrong department. If client has opened the ticket with wrong department then first change the department to correct one and tell client in your reply that he opened ticket with wrong department and teach him that next time he has to open ticket with correct department to get a fast reply.

**Do not provide support for third party softwares**
We do not provide support for third party softwares, if client is having problem then he has to contact his software vendor, we are not responsible if he/she having some problem. But if client still want us to check it then he/she will have to pay remote hand service payment

Refer to pre made reply to check what you need to reply in this case
